FastQ in Bioconductor exercises

Tom Carroll

Installing Bioconductor packages

In these exercises we will review some of the ShortRead packages functionality with handling fastQ files.

The example data can be found in the data directory

Data/sampled_ENCFF000CXH.fastq.gz

We will also use the full FastQ file from this dataset which you can download from here..

  2. Plot the occurrence of A, G, T, C and N in the read with ID “42JV5AAXX_HWI-EAS229_1:6:1:633:2029” using ggplot2

  1. Create a boxplot of quality scores over cycles for reads using base graphics.

  1. Plot the frequency of A, G, C, T and N bases over cycles using ggplot2/

  1. Read in a random 100000 bases from the downloaded ENCFF000CXH.fastq.gz file

  2. Count the number of duplicate sequences and filter file to only the non-duplicated sequences

  3. Trim the resulting non-duplicated reads to remove reads when a succession of 10 bases fall below quality of 5.

  4. Plot a histogram of the resulting read lengths using base graphics
